  "text": "E lectron cryo-microscopy (cryo-EM) has progressed to the point of determining near-atomic resolution maps of macromolecular complexes (for example, see refs 1-3). However, de novo structure determination remains challenging due to initial model bias, map and model overfitting and/or lack of rigorous map and model validation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The ultimate goal of a high-resolution cryo-EM study is to derive all-atom models for the macromolecular components of the assembly that pass the rigorous validation metrics routinely applied to X-ray crystallographic structures [CITATION_3] .",
